  "notes": "The Subsidised Liner is a commercial passenger vessel operating under government subsidy, providing affordable interstellar travel. With 40 luxury staterooms and 10 standard crew staterooms, it can transport up to 40 high-paying passengers in comfort. The ship features extensive common areas including a large lounge, galley, and recreation spaces. Light armament (two beam laser/sandcaster turrets) provides basic defense against pirates. Jump-1 and Thrust-1 performance are adequate for routine commercial routes. The subsidy model requires the ship to accept government charter when needed, but otherwise operates as a commercial passenger liner. High steward complement (1 per 4 passengers) ensures quality service. Medical bay, fuel processor, and launch provide passenger comfort and safety. Low running costs make this an economical passenger transport option."
